    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - TURBOCHARGERS - REMOVAL AND REASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>REMOVAL AND REASSEMBLY</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="8">
            <title>REMOVAL</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the exhaust elbow (
                    <emph type="bold">1, Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150205">2.5</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ), (held with hex-head cap screws, nuts and lock washers.)
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the Turbocharger exhaust sleeve (
                    <emph type="bold">3, Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150205">2.5</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ), located between the exhaust and Turbine housing.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>The exhaust sleeve is loosely held and must be supported when removed.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the turbocharger to intake manifold crossover pipe (as an assembly) and cap the
                    turbo outlet and manifold inlet. (Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150206">2.6</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
                <figure id="ef4150205" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11963" filename="../figcg1/cg11963.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 2.5 Turbocharger Removal.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">1. Exhaust Elbow</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">2. Air-Crossover Tube</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">3. Air Inlet</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">4. Oil-Inlet Tube</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">5. Oil-Outlet Tube</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">6. Exhaust Manifold</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4150206" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg11263" filename="../figcg1/cg11263.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 2.6 Crossover Pipe Removal.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect and remove turbo oil inlet tube assembly at filter header. (See
                    <emph type="bold">Figures
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150207">2.7</hotlnk>
                        and
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150208">2.8</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove tube nut at oil filter header (See
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150207">2.7</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        )
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove the two capscrews from oil inlet tube flange. (See
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150208">2.8</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        )
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove oil inlet tube flange and discard gasket. (See
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150208">2.8</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        )
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove oil inlet tube assembly and discard the rubber sleeve located at the nut
                        end.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Cap turbo oil inlet tube elbow at oil filter header to prevent debris from
                        entering.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Cap ALL openings as specified in
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150210">2.10</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        .
                    </para>
                    <figure id="ef4150207" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="cg11525" filename="../figcg1/cg11525.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 2.7 Removing Turbo Oil Inlet Tube and Sleeve at Oil Inlet Elbow.</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="ef4150208" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="cg11526" filename="../figcg1/cg11526.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 2.8 Removing Capscrews from Turbo Oil Inlet Tube flange.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the turbo oil drain tube as follows: (Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150209">2.9</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Loosen two worm drive hose clamps on turbocharger oil drain tube. (Clamps secure the
                        drain tube hose to the crankcase inlet.)
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove two capscrews and hardened washers which secure the oil drain tube to the
                        turbocharger.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove the oil drain tube and discard the drain tube flange gasket.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove the tube oil drain elbow at the crankcase, if required, and cap (
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150210">2.10</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        ).
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Cap oil drain elbow, if not removed.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Cap oil outlet on turbocharger.</para>
                    <figure id="ef4150209" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="cg11527" filename="../figcg1/cg11527.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 2.9 Removing Turbo Oil Drain Tube.</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="ef4150210" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="cg11528" filename="../figcg1/cg11528.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 2.10 Protective Cap Locations.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove turbocharger assembly from exhaust manifold (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150212">2.12</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove the two turbo mounting bolts with nuts and washers at the lower end of the
                        exhaust manifold flange.
                    </para>
                    <specpara>
                        <caution>
                            <para>SUPPORT THE TURBOCHARGER ASSEMBLY DURING REMOVAL OF THE MOUNTING HARDWARE TO PREVENT
                                DAMAGE.
                            </para>
                        </caution>
                    </specpara>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove the two nuts and washers at the exhaust manifold turbo mounting studs. (Do
                        not remove studs from the exhaust manifold flange.)
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove turbocharger and gasket from engine. Discard gasket.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Assure all turbocharger openings are capped (
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150211">2.11</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        ).
                    </para>
                    <specpara>
                        <note>
                            <para>If plastic caps are available, use duct tape to cover openings.</para>
                        </note>
                    </specpara>
                    <figure id="ef4150211" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="cg11529" filename="../figcg1/cg11529.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 2.11 Install Protective Caps on Turbocharger When Removed for Service.</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="ef4150212" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="cg11410" filename="../figcg1/cg11410.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 2.12 Removing Turbocharger Assembly from Exhaust Manifold.</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
